author: Georgi Kantchev
title: Oil Prices Fall on Crude Oversupply Concerns
text:
LONDON—Oil prices slid on Tuesday pressured by continuing concerns about the global oversupply of crude.
Oil has been trading in a narrow band in recent weeks after falling to more than six-year-lows in the summer on worries about an economic slowdown in China, the world’s second largest consumer of crude.
